5:
Damn! Talk about a brain freeze! I
gotta pace myself better!
8:
You can get shaved ice in Palpebra
too, but there's just something
different about eating it in Yamato!
13:
...Hah! Adventuring is great and all,
but there's nothing wrong with a
little vacation every now and then.
15:
Thanks for bringing me here, you
two.
18:
You're very welcome, Leon. I have a
feeling you'd have come here by
yourself either wayâ€”
21:
Wow! Leon? You could have at least
said hello!
23:
Whoops, my bad. You looked busy,
so I thought I shouldn't bother you.
26: Uh... Leon? Is this a friend of yours?
28:
I sure am! As a matter of fact, Leon
saved my grandfather from a
pickpocket the other day!
31:
I mean, what was I supposed to do?
Pretend I didn't see anything?
34:
Talk about being humble! This guy
was fightin' pickpocket bosses
head-on!
36:
There were so many of 'em, I think I
lost about half my clothes in the
scuffle, though!
39:
Hey, it's Leon! Got some new sake in.
Why don't you drop in sometime?
41:
You hoping to get me drunk and sell
out your whole inventory? Not
gonna work a second time, bud!
45:
I'm starting to get the feeling Leon
knows Yamato a lot better than we
do...
51:
...And we could see ourselves
reflected in the leaves. The Forest of
Mirrors, they called it...
53:
But then! On a single leaf, I noticed
the reflection of a man I had never
seen before!
55:
That gave me a vital clue to help us
escape the forest. Anyone want to
guess what that clue was?
58:
Don't leave us hanging! Come on,
just tell us!
61:
Buy something first! Someone's
gotta help me cover the venue fee!
65: He is like this in Palpebra, too.
68:
I guess this is his idea of a "little
vacation," huh...
74:
Out of my way, tubby! I can't see
anything!
81:
Hey, you two. This guy a friend of
yours?
83:
I heard there was someone around
here worth drawing, but he's much
more popular than I expected!
85:
Mind coming with me for a bit? A
little chat is just the artistic
inspiration I need!
89:
...It was known as the Wandering
Tower. An inexplicable anomaly
appearing only once every hundred
years.
91:
Its gatekeeper, however, is what
posed a problem for us.
94:
It was a man-made giant... A blue
metal golem so massive my sword
could barely reach its waist.
101:
Of course, I couldn't get it to listen to
reason, and it swiftly attacked us.
104:
I took the golem head-on, while my
partner Herman...
107:
Hey, Alk. Pretend there's a golem
standing there, and you're right
behind it!
112:
H-huh? Here? Uhh, can we go
somewhere a little less cluttered?
119:
Perfect! That's exactly how Herman
managed to strike the golem's weak
spot.
124:
All right, Alk! Do that thing again,
and don't stop until I say so!
133:
Excellent! The creative juices are
really flowing now!
145:
Yeah, that geezer looked just like
this! You even nailed his freaky smile!
149:
...Yeah. Herman really did smile like
this.
153:
Ah, shoot. I thought I remembered
all my old buddies better than this.
155:
Yet here I am, forgetting how they
looked... Forgetting their smiles.
160:
So that move you taught me was
Herman's, huh.
163:
He had the same build as you and
carried his sword the same way too.
Totally different smile, though!
166:
...When you and I first met, I'd
sometimes see Herman when I
watched you fight.
168:
Not anymore, though. When we
fight, I just see you, Alk.
175:
Of course I do. Watching you fight
against the Purgers and defy the
odds is proof enough of your own
ability.
179:
Oh! So you were one of the
adventurers who joined the Purger
battle!
182:
Course I was! A friend in need is a
friend indeed, right?
187:
Hold on, you two! A fight with...
Purgers, you say? Now THAT sounds
inspiring!
190:
I'd love to tell you all about it, but I'm
afraid Alk was the main character in
that adventure!
193:
...What do you say, Alk? Mind telling
us your story?
197:
Heh... It's not just MY story. I had a lot
of friends helping me along the way.
Stella was also a real trooper.
202: Indeed. We all worked hard together.
207:
Hah! I thought you'd say that. In that
case, tell me the WHOLE story of
your big adventure...
210:
...and include every single one of
those comrades you can brag
about!
